Armed bandits yesterday kidnapped six persons from Gurin, a border community with Cameroon in Fufore Local Government Area in Adamawa State. Residents revealed that a group of armed men thronged the village in the morning and took six young men. But while residents claimed six persons were abducted, the police said it was three. OVER 5,000 NIGERIAN MEN HAVE  OVERCOME POOR BEDROOM PERFORMANCE SYNDROME DUE TO THIS BRILLIANT DISCOVERY Confirming the incident, the spokesman for Adamawa State Police Command, Deputy Superintendent of Police (DSP), Sulaiman Nguroje said the attackers initially abducted four persons but freed one of them to take the information home.  Gunmen kidnap 6 persons in Adamawa Boko Haram kills 11 in Adamawa How Armed men abducted six female students, two teachers in Kaduna